<p>  A count (rather than a percentage completion graph) of the number of records transcribed for each event and year <a href="http://www.freebmd.org.uk/cgi/EntryCounts.pl" target="_blank">is available here (opens in a new Window).</a> </p>
 <p>  Please note that the percentage completions are based on <strong>estimates</strong> and, in particular, a value of 100% does not guarantee that all entries have been transcribed. See below for further information.</p>
<h2> How the percentages are calculated</h2>
<p>  The percentage coverage shown in the above graphs is only an estimate for the following reasons:</p>
<ul class="push=half-bottom">
<li> The total number of entries in a year is based on GRO figures which may not be accurate</li>
<li> The GRO gives the total number of entries for deaths in a year, only to the nearest thousand</li>
<li> In view of this, the percentages can be up to 2 percentage points out, for example a percentage of 60% could in reality be anything between 58% and 62%.</li>
</ul>